The paper deals with the problem of estimating the probability of meeting a deadline in a hierarchical plan with uncertain task times. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for planning and scheduling, data structures (cs.DS) for representing the plan, robotics (cs.RO) for task planning, machine learning (cs.LG) for probabilistic modeling, and systems and control (cs.SY) for control of systems with uncertain dynamics.
